	</div>
</div>		<div class="text">
			The structure of the song is based on an old folk song called "Lord Randall." The chorus is of his mother asking "Where have you been Lord Randall my son? Where have you been my handsome young man?" I think it's on the Library of Congress' "Appalachian Folk Traditions" recorded by Alan Lomax. I don't have it in front of me right now so please excuse any inaccuacy in detail. This doesn't exactly explain why Dylan changed the lyric to "blue eyed son" but thought you might find it interesting anyway.			<div class="sign">

				<span id="flagspan-73016152769">
											<a href="#" id="flag-73016152769" class="flag">Flag</a>
										</span>



